article.headline: Siena 84, Rider 62
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Clarence Jackson and Alex Franklin scored 22 points each to lead Siena to an 84-62 victory over Rider on Wednesday night. Franklin added 11 rebounds and the Saints (7-4, 2-0 Metro Athletic Atlantic Conference) rolled to a 46-30 halftime lead on their way to winning their 25th consecutive home game. Siena shot 57.6 percent from the field (19-for-33) in the first half and gradually pulled away from Rider (8-6, 1-1), taking a 44-28 lead on Franklin's two free throws with 1:33 left. Edwin Ubiles' 3-pointer gave the Saints a 56-33 advantage with 17:15 left in the game. Ubiles finished with 13 points and Ryan Rossiter added 12 points and 10 rebounds for the Saints. Siena's Ronald Moore, who entered leading Division I with eight assists a game, had 12. Mike Ringgold led Rider with 16 points and 12 rebounds. Justin Robinson added 11 points and Novar Gadson had 10.
